brain activities. The core task is classification, regarding if a 
sample indicates a seizure activity. The number of features 
and samples are 179 and 11500, respectively. Almost 20% 
of the samples are categorized as seizure activity. So, we are 
dealing with an unbalanced dataset in a binary classifica-
tion setting. The first 178 features are the values of the Elec-
troencephalogram (EEG) recordings at different time points, 
and the last feature is the class. There are five values for 
the class label (y = 1, ..., 5). Except for y = 1, the rest of 
the classes indicate subjects who do not have an epileptic 
seizure. Dataset statistics are given in Table 1.
